  "body": "Remix JavaScript VM consumes much more RAM than HardHat local node in testing a reentrancy transaction. And the browser crash frequently when running a large test.\r\n\r\n## Results Comparision\r\n| Settings             | Task                          | RAM Usage |\r\n|----------------------|-------------------------------|-----------|\r\n| Remix + JSVM         | Test 4 in puzzle 2 (attached) | ~1.5 GiB   |\r\n| Remix + HardHat Node | Same as above                 | < 10 MiB  |\r\n| HardHat test         | Same as above                 | ~60MiB    |\r\n\r\nAttached is the screenshot of Remix and task manager indicating the RAM usage increase (each row is ~1.6 GiB and running it takes 1 row in the RAM graph).\r\n![The screenshot of Remix and task manager indicating the RAM usage increase.](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/101602845/167506485-b1e33e62-2427-4f87-850a-bc3ca33d77e7.png)\r\n\r\n## Configuration\r\n1. Remix Verison: Remix 0.23.3 \r\n2. JSVM version: London\r\n3. HardHat: 2.0.5\r\n4. Browser: Chrome 101.0.4951.54\r\n\r\n## How to Replicate\r\n1. Clone https://github.com/ryestew/gamedayRemix to your local/remix IDE;\r\n2. Open `tests/js_test/puzzle2.test.js` and modify Line 21:\r\n```js\r\nconst ONE_TEN_TOKEN = ethers.utils.parseUnits(\"40.0\", 18); // change to \"40.0\", so the reenter happens 8 times; or you can go bigger\r\nconst initialSupply = ONE_TEN_TOKEN;\r\n```\r\n3. Run the test\r\n    1. Run it on Remix with JSVM: compile all files in `contracts/puzzle2` and go to `tests/js_test/puzzle2.test.js`, right-click and run.\r\n    2. Run it on Remix with local HH node: install hardhat in local (`npm install`) and start a node `npx hardhat node`, go to 3.1 to run test\r\n    3. Run it on local HH: `npx hardhat test tests/js_tests/puzzle2.test.js`\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
